lo` (Initial, X25519 pubkey) → `ServerHello` (Handshake, X25519 pubkey + AEAD selection) → `HANDSHAKE_DONE` (1-RTT). Transcript hashing for key derivation. Phase 6: 0-RTT resumption via session tickets.\n\n**`ack.c`** — ACK/loss detection. Tracks sent packets (up to 1024), received PN ranges (up to 64), RTT estimation (smoothed + variance + min), RACK-style time-based loss detection, PTO (Probe Timeout), delayed ACK timer (25ms).\n\n**`stream.c`** — Stream send/recv buffer management. Offset-based byte stream with retransmission support (`on_loss` rewinds `sent_offset`).\n\n**`flow_control.c`** — Connection-level and per-stream flow control. Tracks `peer_max_data` / `local_max_data`, auto-sends `MAX_DATA` updates when window is half consumed.\n\n**`scheduler.c`** — Round-robin stream scheduler using a circular doubly-linked list. `nxp_sched_next()` picks the next stream with unsent data.\n\n**`migration.c`** / **`migration_internal.h`** — Connection migration: PATH_CHALLENGE/RESPONSE path validation, CID pool management (up to 8 peer CIDs), NEW_CONNECTION_ID / RETIRE_CONNECTION_ID frame handling. CID routing support (node ID prefix for load balancers).\n\n**`listener.c`** / **`listener_internal.h`** — Multi-connection server. CID → `nxp_conn*` hash map routing. Stateless Retry support. Round-robin send loop. Per-IP rate limiting (100 pps/IP, 1s window). Up to 4096 concurrent connections by default.\n\n**`heartbeat.c`** — HEARTBEAT frame (0x20) keep-alive. Configurable interval, 3-miss dead detection, RTT measurement via echo timestamps.\n\n**`session_export.c`** — Serialize/deserialize connection state for server-to-server migration. Exports CIDs, crypto keys, flow control, RTT estimates. Wire format is little-endian with magic `\"NXPS\"`.\n\n**`rate_limit.h`** — Per-IP DoS rate limiter (header-only, token bucket via hash map).\n\n**`stream_rate.h`** — Per-stream token-bucket rate limiter (header-only). 100ms burst, configurable bytes/sec.\n\n**`heartbeat_internal.h